1EEKg">pic.twitter.com/vrSU11EEKg</a></p>— Senator John Cornyn (@JohnCornyn) <a href="https://twitter.com/JohnCornyn/status/1103822591540776963?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">March 8, 2019</a> </blockquote> <script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script> </div> <p>Joe Biden's former chief of staff reacted to reports of Jared Kushner&nbsp;shutting out U.S. diplomats in Saudi Arabia:</p> <div class="inline-content inline-photo inline-photo-center horizontal-photo"> <blockquote class="twitter-tweet"> <p lang="en" dir="ltr">When Jared Kushner travels overseas, he's not doing America's business -- he's doing Jared Kushner's business. No one should believe otherwise. <a href="https://t.co/szemNcBoqw">https://t.co/szemNcBoqw</a></p>— Ronald Klain (@RonaldKlain) <a href="https://twitter.com/RonaldKlain/status/1103675757988143105?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">March 7, 2019</a> </blockquote> <script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script> </div> <p>Columnist Connie Schultz, who is married to Sen. Sherrod Brown (D-Ohio), reflected on his decision to not run for president:</p> <div class="inline-content inline-photo inline-photo-center horizontal-photo"> <blockquote class="twitter-tweet"> <p lang="en" dir="ltr">I support my husband, always.<br><br>It will surprise no one, I suspect, to know that I still think <a href="https://twitter.com/SenSherrodBrown?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@SenSherrodBrown</a> would be a wonderful president. <a href="https://t.co/8pRoW6A9iW">https://t.co/8pRoW6A9iW</a></p>— Connie Schultz (@ConnieSchultz) <a href="https://twitter.com/ConnieSchultz/status/1103712194066300929?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">March 7, 2019</a> </blockquote> <script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script> </div> <p>Sen. Cory Booker (D-N.J.) applauded his colleague's work after he said he would remain in the Senate:</p> <div class="inline-content inline-photo inline-photo-center horizontal-photo"> <b